{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Psyked: James' Web Development website","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"97b3bf07-0b99-584b-9c00-08230e4e4e0a","html":"<p>As I've been playing around with the ApplicationInfo class, I thought my Splash Screen stuff would be so much nicer if it were a little more... generic?</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3f4636bfc6e4b51499575d0524da1b47/48a11/mysplashscreen2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"mysplashscreen2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3f4636bfc6e4b51499575d0524da1b47/48a11/mysplashscreen2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3f4636bfc6e4b51499575d0524da1b47/3b5c6/mysplashscreen2.jpg 158w,\n/static/3f4636bfc6e4b51499575d0524da1b47/434a1/mysplashscreen2.jpg 315w,\n/static/3f4636bfc6e4b51499575d0524da1b47/48a11/mysplashscreen2.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>So with that in mind, I've updated my Flex Splash screen project to impliment the <a href=\"http://psyked-as-classes.googlecode.com/files/applicationinfo.zip\">ApplicationInfo class</a>, and use that to load information such as the version numbers, application names and application icons. Â Maybe it's not the most efficent way to do things, but what the hell, it's a good example for implimenting the ApplicationInfo class.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2008/12/splash-screen-demo-2.zip\">Download the updated Splash Screen example Flex project here.</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"My Splash Screen example - updated with ApplicationInfo class","date":"December 02, 2008","tags":["air","applicationinfo"],"url":null,"image":null,"description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/resize-multiple-images-and-package-them-for-e-mail-transmission-introducing-imagesizer/","tags":["imagesizer","air","fzip"],"title":"Resize multiple images and package them for e-mail transmission - introducing ImageSizer!","date":"2008-12-02T11:45:30.000Z","description":null,"image":null}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/executing-multiple-xmlhttprequests-successfully/","tags":["javascript","ajax","xmlhttprequest"],"title":"Executing multiple XMLHTTPRequests - successfully.","date":"2008-12-03T12:15:30.000Z","description":null,"image":null}}}}